| **8-9** | Frontend Adaptation | Adapt existing React app to connect Polkadot wallets, build DID management UI, implement publishing workflow, create verification tool |
| **10** | E2E Testing & CI | Write end-to-end test suite, set up GitHub Actions CI/CD, run frontend E2E tests with Cypress, fix bugs discovered during testing |
| **11** | Documentation | Write all docs (README, ARCHITECTURE, DEPLOYMENT, TESTING, VERIFICATION, THREAT_MODEL), internal code review, record walkthrough video |
| **12** | Final Delivery | Publish article to Medium/Polkadot blog, create GitHub release `v0.1.0-fastgrant`, submit delivery PR, announce publicly |

**Key Milestones:**

- **Week 4:** Contract working locally (we can register publications and verify them via script)
- **Week 7:** Full stack deployed on testnets (Shibuya + Peregrine), integration tests passing
- **Week 9:** Frontend demo live at public URL
- **Week 12:** All deliverables complete, documented, and verified

**Risk Mitigation:**

- **KILT testnet downtime:** We run local KILT node via Docker for development; only use Peregrine for final integration testing
- **Contract deployment issues:** Extensive local testing on Swanky Node before touching Shibuya
- **IPFS gateway unreliability:** Three fallback gateways configured; tests pass even if one gateway is down
- **Wallet integration bugs:** Buffer week (week 10) specifically allocated for bug fixes and polish based on E2E test results

