## Additional Information

**How We Found Fast-Grants:**  
Through Polkadot's grants page and recommendations from the KILT Protocol community. After our Algorand integration didn't work out due to identity infrastructure limitations, we started researching Polkadot parachains and discovered KILT. Their documentation pointed us to Fast-Grants as the right funding path for contract-based projects.

**Prior Work (Unfunded Development):**

- 8 months of threat modeling, technical specifications, and architecture design
- Partnerships established with Committee to Protect Journalists and Reporters Without Borders (MOU signed for future credential issuance; awaiting production deployment)
- User research with 30+ journalists in Mexico, Russia, and Hong Kong (identifying UX requirements, threat models, operational security needs)
- Proof-of-concept implementations on Algorand (frontend works, contracts deployed, but identity layer inadequate) and Zcash exploration (privacy strong, programmability weak)
- Existing React frontend already built and tested with real users: https://github.com/Emilio983/SocialMask/tree/main/main-site

**What We Learned From Previous Integrations:**

Our Algorand version proved journalists understand the UX (connect wallet → create pseudonym → publish → verify). But without standardized DIDs and verifiable credentials, we couldn't scale beyond test groups. Zcash taught us that privacy alone isn't enough — we need composability and developer tools.

Polkadot's multi-chain architecture solves both problems: KILT provides W3C-compliant identity infrastructure, Astar provides mature smart contract deployment, and we can compose them without building everything ourselves.

**Parallel Grant Applications:**

- **Zcash Community Grants** (privacy payment layer) – Status: Pending
